a(S'A useful way to examine how art history is organized is through the major survey textbooks, which reflect an encyclopedic view of great art. Frequently consulted textbooks published in English are Ernst Gombrich  s Story of Art, Marilyn Stokstad  s Art History, Anthony Janson  s History of Art, David Wilkins, Bernard Schultz, and Katheryn M. Linduff  s Art Past, Art Present, Helen Gardner  s Art Through the Ages, Hugh Honour and John Flemming  s A World History of Art, and Laurie Schneider Adams  s Art Across Time. One of the best places to find information on canonical art history is the Heilbrunn Timeline of Art History, sponsored by the Metropolitan Museum of Art in New York.'
