a(S'Programming language'
p2357
g2082
tp2358
a(S'Main article: Programming language'
p2359
g2082
tp2360
a(S'Programming languages provide various ways of specifying programs for computers to run. Unlike natural languages, programming languages are designed to permit no ambiguity and to be concise. They are purely written languages and are often difficult to read aloud. They are generally either translated into machine code by a compiler or an assembler before being run, or translated directly at run time by an interpreter. Sometimes programs are executed by a hybrid method of the two techniques.'
p2361
g2082
tp2362
a(g6
g2082
tp2363
a(S'Low level languages'
p2364
g2082
tp2365
a(S'Main article: Low level programming language'
p2366
g2082
tp2367
a(S'Machine languages and the assembly languages that represent them (collectively termed low level programming languages) tend to be unique to a particular type of computer. For instance, an ARM architecture computer (such as may be found in a PDA or a hand held videogame) cannot understand the machine language of an Intel Pentium or the AMD Athlon 64 computer that might be in a PC.[59]'
p2368
g2082
tp2369
a(g6
g2082
tp2370
a(S'High level languages/Third Generation Language'
p2371
g2082
tp2372
a(S'Main article: High level programming language'
p2373
g2082
tp2374
a(S'Though considerably easier than in machine language, writing long programs in assembly language is often difficult and is also error prone. Therefore, most practical programs are written in more abstract high level programming languages that are able to express the needs of the programmer more conveniently (and thereby help reduce programmer error). High level languages are usually "compiled" into machine language (or sometimes into assembly language and then into machine language) using another computer program called a compiler.[60] High level languages are less related to the workings of the target computer than assembly language, and more related to the language and structure of the problem(s) to be solved by the final program. It is therefore often possible to use different compilers to translate the same high level language program into the machine language of many different types of computer. This is part of the means by which software like video games may be made available for different computer architectures such as personal computers and various video game consoles.'
p2375
g2082
tp2376
a(g6
g2082
tp2377
a(S'Fourth Generation Languages'
p2378
g2082
tp2379
a(S'These 4G languages are less procedural than 3G languages. The benefit of 4GL is that it provides ways to obtain information without requiring the direct help of a programmer. Example of 4GL is SQL.'
p2380
g2082
tp2381
a(g6
