tp3972
a(S'The analysis and study of algorithms is a discipline of computer science, and is often practiced abstractly without the use of a specific programming language or '
p3973
g2082
tp3974
a(S'implementation. In this sense, algorithm analysis resembles other mathematical disciplines in that it focuses on the underlying properties of the algorithm and not on the '
p3975
g2082
tp3976
a(S'specifics of any particular implementation. Usually pseudocode is used for analysis as it is the simplest and most general representation. However, ultimately, most '
p3977
g2082
